The Mojo circuit proves:

· The witness contains a valid Ed25519 signature from author_public_key over credential.
· The credential’s licensee_pubkey equals the public key derived from licensee_private_key.
· The credential’s policy_commitment matches the public input policy_commitment.

---

5. Groth16 Circuit Description (High-Level)

Public inputs: author_pubkey, policy_commitment, licensee_pubkey
Private witness: credential, signature, licensee_privkey

Constraints:

1. licensee_pubkey == public_key_derive(licensee_privkey)
2. credential.licensee_pubkey == licensee_pubkey
3. credential.policy_commitment == policy_commitment
4. verify_ed25519(signature, author_pubkey, serialize(credential)) == true

The circuit does not reveal the credential content; only the public ids and policy hash are disclosed. To generate this, you can use a ZK framework like Circom with an Ed25519 gadget, or rely on Mojo’s own constraint system. The exact implementation is outside this document but follows this spec.

